description:
&lt;p&gt;The Private Patients Unit is seeking an experienced Private Patients Inpatient Administration Coordinator with excellent communication skills who is customer focused with previous private inpatients coordination and administration experience preferably within a NHS environment. Reporting to the Private Patients Unit Inpatients Administration Supervisor, you will be responsible for administering the Private Patients Unit’s inpatients’ services and reception daily functions. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Working a variable rota that runs Saturdays to Mondays from 7am to 8pm, you will be responsible for manning the inpatients’ reception and carrying out the daily administrative functions including inpatient and theatre bookings as well as insurance authorisations. You will engage with; patients, consultants, referrers and external providers as well as staff members across all other departments within the wider trust to provide them with world class care customer service. You will be responsible for covering for the Private Patients Administration Coordinator– Outpatients/Enquiries whilst on annual leave. An impeccable telephone and email manner and confidence in dealing with people at all levels are essential. You should be a team player, meticulous, detail oriented and enthusiastic with the ability to work in a challenging and changing environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will have a working knowledge of Compucare, Cerner, CRIS, EDRM, IRRIS, EPR and Microsoft Office&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name:Linnea Pettersson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Inpatients and Admissions Administration Supervisor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Linnea.Pettersson@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
